In 431 my restoration is accepted by Munro, Baehrens, and Sudhaus, pingui scatet ubere sulphur ¹. But should this verse be connected with 430 or with 432? I prefer the former view, ‘the volcanic district between Cumae and N aples has for many years ceased to burn, in spite of the sulphur, which is there so abundant as to be collected for purposes of sale! Daubeny, p. 317, makes the same remark about the islet of Nisyros. ‘The sulphur is so abundant as to be collected as an article of com- merce, and is occasionally exported to Smyrna!
